
Overview of adj chronic

The adj chronic has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (9) chronic -- (being long-lasting and recurrent or characterized by long suffering; "chronic indigestion"; "a chronic shortage of funds"; "a chronic invalid")
2. chronic, continuing -- (of long duration; "chronic money problems")
3. chronic, inveterate -- (habitual; "a chronic smoker")
